The Standard Organisation of Nigeria (SON) has warned dealers of cables and wire products from selling substandard products to unsuspecting buyers. The Gombe State Coordinator of the agency, Umar Yakubu gave the warning yesterday during market surveillance to the shops of wire and cable dealers in Gombe metropolis. He said SON embarked on the inspection to conduct regular tests and ensure that the products sold to members of the public meet required standard. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The coordinator added that they were at the markets following a report that substandard cables are being moved to Gombe from other states. SON confiscates electric substandard cables worth N1m in Yobe Kogi: SON clamps down on substandard cable dealers SON confiscates substandard cables in Borno